version_description: Corrected chords and alignment over lyrics, simplified playing by adding capo.

The correct version of the new Linkin Park song, which is a simple, by-the-books, very safe pop song - nothing revolutionary here. Good song tho, although not sure about the verses, pretty sure its just arpeggios of the B chord, but it migh be jumping around like: I-V-I. Other than that, everything else is correct. No strumming pattern since its mostly produced. Enjoy, be sure to edit if something's wrong.
This song is in the key of Bb. Transcribed from the studio version.

This version has been transcribed by ear using the stems of the original song. These are the original chords of the song, in the original key. All the others versions on the site so far were transposed into different keys, with different chords. Chords also in a more specific arrangement, so the performer has a better idea of when to switch.
I made this because I couldn't find the correct chords for this song in my acoustic guitar. I did this song with a capo in 1st fret.
This version uses power chords to make it easy to play for everyone. It also uses capo on 4th to enable playing it with the record if desired to.
First live version ( Emotinal version from Southside Festival 2017 ).
